CCS Students - your teachers, support staff, and administration are SUPER PROUD OF YOU!!

You did an AMAZING job on your first day back at school. I know the mask thing is a pain...however, it gets us back together in school where we belong.

CCS Parents - thanks for your help preparing your kids for coming back to school and being able to manage the new way of doing school. You should be proud of your kiddos.

CCS Teachers - thank you for making adjustments to your physical classroom spaces so most rooms are able to be mask free during instruction.

Let’s keep it going!! Remember - I wear a mask to protect you, and you wear a mask to protect me.
Mr. Groff

Parent School Reopening Survey

Each family should have received a phone blast message regarding the district’s request for parents to complete the Parent School Reopening Survey.

If not, please be sure to visit the school’s website for a link to the survey. It is located on the front page of the website. https://www.ccsdny.org/

The survey includes vital information that will be necessary for students, parents and the school district to be able to prepare for in-person instruction in September. Only one survey is requested per household.

Parents / students / staff / school community: I want to let you know that our school district has created its Returning to Instruction Plan as required by NYS. The plan has been posted to our school website - with a link on the front page.

If the guidance changes from NYS, we will evaluate the plan and make any necessary changes. Any applicable changes will be updated on the website.

Please be sure to read through the plan so students and parents understand the protocols and procedures that will be put in place for September.

Thanks
Mr. Groff

From the Canaseraga Fall Harvest Festival Committee:
It is with great sadness that we announce the 2020 Canaseraga Fall Harvest Festival has been cancelled. After much discussion, it was decided the safety of our community comes first. The rules and regulations supplied to us by the county were very extensive and it would be nearly impossible for us to keep in compliance. Thank you for your continued support as we look forward to next year. Save the date: September 18 & 19, 2021.

post_text:
Deadline for Voting with Absentee Ballots Extended

The following is by executive order from the NYS Governor 06/08/2020:

•Sections 2018-a and 2018-b of the Education Law, to the extent necessary to allow any absentee ballot for an election held on June 9, 2020 and received by mail in the office of the clerk of the school district or designee of the trustees or school board not later than June 16, 2020 to be canvassed for such election.

No ballots for such election shall be accepted by the clerk of the school district or designee of the trustees or school board after 5 p.m. on June 9, 2020 except those received by mail in accordance with this provision.

Any receptacle used for hand delivery of absentee ballots in such election shall be closed and removed at 5 p.m. on June 9, 2020;

The ballots therein shall remain unopened pending delivery of mailed ballots, and shall be removed and canvassed after 5 p.m. on June 16, 2020

Don't forget we have a GooseChase at 11! Looking for some family fun? Who will be crowned this week's Goosechase winner? Mr. K will be hosting another fun virtual scavenger hunt on Thursday (4/9) at 11am. Here's what you need to know if you want to participate.

1. Download the GooseChase iOS or Android app. (one device is needed per family/team)

2. Choose to play as a guest.

3. Search by game code JW8V3K (Canaseraga Scavenger Hunt - Part 3)
4. Enter your name so Mr. K knows who it is and follow the prompts to allow camera/microphone on your phone/device.

Goosechase is a virtual scavenger hunt allows you to take pictures or videos of missions for points. Mr. K will be moderating the game and bonus points will be awarded for unique/creative answers. Remember this is a family friendly event where Mr. K and other teams will be able to see you missions that you submit. Please be logged in and ready to go before 11am- the game will start promptly at 11am and you will have an hour to complete as many missions as you can. Good luck!

post_text: Congratulations to AC BRAGGS 1N C0DE!!!!
shared_text:
Braggs 1N C0DE
March 2 at 7:24 AM ·

Congratulations to the AC BRAGGS 1N C0DE Robotics team! On Saturday, Feb. 29, 2020, the team traveled to Syracuse, NY to compete in the Northern New York State Championship. Despite, the tough competition, the team was awarded the EDUCATE Award based on their interview with the judges. The judges were impressed with the young team coming together from two schools to create a partnership, overcoming scheduling obstacles, the mentorship program between Alfred University and our students, getting more students involved and the selflessness of team and coach. Team members include: Jaden Lang, Logan Garfield, Valerie Miller, Noel Roman, Nic Gates, Mia Lang, Gaelen Lang, Alec Briggs, and Gavin Crane.
Galen Lang and Alec Briggs were volunteers at the championship and helped to reset the fields after each match, parent volunteer-Trevor Garfield, was an emcee and Mrs. Briggs was a judge for the VEX IQ Championship.

R E S C H E D U L E D
E V E N T

Retired Canaseraga Athletic Uniforms will be available on:

TUESDAY, JANUARY 21, 5:30pm - 7:00pm, Cafeteria

The school board has approved the distribution of our retired Indian athletic uniforms and to make them available to our school community - at no charge. Any remaining uniforms will be donated to a mission trip going to Guatemala. We have 20+ bins of uniforms that will be available.

We have uniforms available from Cheerleading, Baseball / Softball, Soccer, Basketball, a couple Golf polos, warm-ups, and basketball practice jerseys.

The uniforms will be grouped by sport, but not separated by gender. If you know someone who would like to have a uniform they once wore, please share this with them. There will be no "reserving" of particular uniforms / numbers. It will be first come, first grab.

Please feel free to share this with others in the school community.

post_text: Canaseraga's Educational Technology Specialists -Craig Kaczmarek and Kristi Briggs presented at the annual NYSCATE Conference with fellow educators from Port Byron to a packed house!
shared_text:
Penny Brock Mills is with Jennifer Roden and 2 others.
November 26, 2019 at 11:12 AM ·

We did it!!! After years of attending and sitting in audiences—we found the courage to move to the front of the room. So honored to share our journey and knowledge with others. Hoping to inspire 💕🌎💕. 8:45am packed session with people standing and on the floor made me crazy nervous, not going to lie;) But we did it!! 😊. Proud to be a part of the FunFriends group #NYSCATE19.

shared_text:
Career Development Council
October 29, 2019 at 10:59 AM ·

Career Development Council coordinated with Canaseraga Central School, Mrs. Neff’s 1st grade students to bring in a classroom presenter on Yoga. The students participated in a full yoga session, breathing, stretching, and bending aka as the tree, the airplane and downward dog formations just to name a few positions. They also worked on breathing techniques to ensure calmness and how to center themselves to focus.
“It was incredible. Brooke really connected to the students and taught them about being thankful in their lives.” said Mrs. Neff. The 1st graders will continue these exercises daily in the classroom.

post_text:
Alec Hurlbut Places 6th at National Skills Leadership Conference

CONGRATULATIONS to 2019 graduate Alec Hurlbut on his 6th place finish at the National Skills Leadership Conference in Louisville, Kentucky. Alec competed with 43 other students in the Diesel Equipment Technology Trouble Shooting contest. He was tasked with diagnosing repair issues at 14 different stations that included engine transmission, electrical, brakes, steering, hydraulics, and computer engine controls.

Alec participated in the Heavy Equipment program on the GST BOCES Wildwood Vocational Campus during his junior and senior years. Alec’s hard work over the past two years paid off in the form of competing at the national level, and being named the 2018-19 Student of the Year for the Wildwood Campus.

Great job Alec!! Keep up the hard work and dedication to your skills. Thank you for representing your Canaseraga school community so well.

post_text: On June 5th, Daniel Jude Miller D.Jude Miller Publishing will visit our school. He is a self-published author, illustrator, speaker and graphic artist from Binghamton, New York. He grew up in New York City and that is the back drop for his Monsters in Manhattan Series. These creative books tell the story of a narrator whose cousins come to visit and he is in charge of showing them around the sights of New York City. He figures out the perfect way to ensure their early departure. His other two books Everybody Wake Up and Halloween Boy and the Christmas Kid are equally entertaining. He will speak to grades pre-k through 6 in four presentations in the library. This year we are not taking pre-orders for his books but he will be bringing orders with him and students that wish to purchase an autographed book can order it and have it delivered to the school at a later date. We are all looking forward to his visit!
